getAllBindings

OWLIndividualList<Binding<?>> getAllBindings()
Returns all data flow bindings within this composite process. It does not distinguish whether the flow is coming from outside into the process or the flow is completely embedded into the process or the flow goes from the process out to some outside perform.

Returns:
A list of bindings that have at least their source or sink in this process.

isInvocable

boolean isInvocable()
Invocable is a flag that tells whether this composite process bottoms out in atomic processes. If so, it is "invocable", as soon as there is a SimpleProcess it is no longer invocable.

Note that this flag should not be mixed up with whether a composite process is executable as simple processes are indirectly executable.

Note that OWL-S has a dedicated property to make this information explicit. However, implementations should rather compute the boolean value dynamically by traversing the entire control constructs hierarchy and check if leave nodes are atomic processes; i.e., consider this property as synthetic. (This is also the reason why there is no setter method for this property.)

Returns:
true if this composite process bottoms out in atomic processes.
